Parliament, Monday, 12 March 2018 – The Standing Committee on Appropriations will tomorrow hold public hearings on the 2018 Division of Revenue Bill. The Committee is to receive public comments on the Bill, which seeks to provide for the equitable division of revenue raised nationally among the national, provincial and local spheres of government for the 2018/19 financial year. Details of the public hearings are as follows: Date: Tuesday, 13 March 2018
	Time: 10 am
	Venue: GH41, Good Hope Building ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE COMMITTEE, MS YVONNE PHOSA For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer:
	Name: Ms Felicia LombardParliamentary Communication ServicesTel: 021 403 8285Cell: 081 548 7011E-mail: flombard@parliament.gov.za The seat of Parliament is in Cape Town, but it could be moved by an Act of Parliament supported by a majority of the members of the National Assembly.Read more